  "chapter": {
    "number": 26,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Similitudes and Instructions"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Like snow in summer and rain at harvest,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "honor does not befit a fool.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Like a fluttering sparrow or darting swallow,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "an undeserved curse does not come to rest.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A whip for the horse, a bridle for the donkey,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and a rod for the backs of fools!",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Do not answer a fool according to his folly,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or you yourself will be like him.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Answer a fool according to his folly,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "lest he become wise in his own eyes.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Like cutting off one’s own feet or drinking violence",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "is the sending of a message by the hand of a fool.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Like lame legs hanging limp",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "is a proverb in the mouth of a fool.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Like binding a stone into a sling",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "is the giving of honor to a fool.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Like a thorn that falls into the hand of a drunkard",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "is a proverb in the mouth of a fool.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Like an archer who wounds at random",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "is he who hires a fool or passerby.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "As a dog returns to its vomit,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4257
          },
          {
            "text": "so a fool repeats his folly.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Do you see a man who is wise in his own eyes?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "There is more hope for a fool than for him.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The slacker says, “A lion is in the road!",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "A fierce lion roams the public square!”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "As a door turns on its hinges,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so the slacker turns on his bed.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The slacker buries his hand in the dish;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "it wearies him to bring it back to his mouth.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The slacker is wiser in his own eyes",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "than seven men who answer discreetly.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Like one who grabs a dog by the ears",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "is a passerby who meddles in a quarrel not his own.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Like a madman shooting firebrands",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and deadly arrows,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "so is the man who deceives his neighbor",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and says, “I was only joking!”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Without wood, a fire goes out;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "without gossip, a conflict ceases.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Like charcoal for embers and wood for fire,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so is a quarrelsome man for kindling strife.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The words of a gossip are like choice morsels",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "that go down into the inmost being.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Like glaze covering an earthen vessel",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "are burning",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4258
          },
          {
            "text": "lips and a wicked heart.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 24,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A hateful man disguises himself with his speech,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "but he lays up deceit in his heart.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 25,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "When he speaks graciously, do not believe him,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for seven abominations fill his heart.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 26,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Though his hatred is concealed by deception,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "his wickedness will be exposed in the assembly.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 27,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He who digs a pit will fall into it,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and he who rolls a stone will have it roll back on him.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 28,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A lying tongue hates those it crushes,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and a flattering mouth causes ruin.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
